the stoic 中文翻譯
中文翻譯手機版斯多噶stoic:    adj. 1.斯多噶學派的。 2.〔s-〕＝stoica ...stoic:    adj. 1.斯多噶學派的。 2.〔s-〕＝stoical. n. 斯多噶學派的人；〔s-〕 禁欲(主義)者。 stoic swordsman:    禁欲的劍客the stolen bag:    被偷去的包the stocky stonemason:    肥胖的石匠420the stolen child:    被拐走的孩子; 失竊的孩子the stocks slumped:    股票價格狂跌the stolen children:    小小偷的春天the stocks issued to domestic investors:    採取記名股票形式the stolen farthings:    偷藏的錢the stockades:    監獄the stolen horse:    被偷的馬the stock-transfer system:    股票轉讓制度
例句與用法" he expressed the stoic observation that " everything changed on 9 - 11"他表示斯多葛觀察認為， "一切都改變了對9 - 11 。 I ' m living like the stoic bird , man . - it ' s the only way to live , son-我活得就像堅忍的鳥兒。 -這是生存的唯一方式，年輕人。 The stoic individuals who ventured to the frontier were reverently referred to as pioneers , individuals who embodied the true character of the nation那些前往邊境冒險堅忍的民眾被景仰為先驅，他們具體表現了這個國家的真實性格。 In the 4th century b . c . , four schools of philosophers often argued with each , they were the cynics , the sceptics , the epicureans , and the stoics公元前四世紀，西方哲學四大利派相互爭鳴，這四大流派為：犬儒主義學派、懷疑論學派、伊壁鳩魯派（享樂主義學派） 、斯多葛學派。 The stoic takes risks greatly the game is introduced : quite interesting stoic ' s game , the stoic in saying has and strange fish which the brain exposed , the sick one is blamed stickily and the small pig piece together a life - and - death , will not continue advancing unless dive under water on the right to get the key while beginning忍者大冒險游戲介紹：相當有趣的忍者游戲，居然傳說中的忍者不得不和大腦外露的怪魚，惡心的黏稠怪以及小豬玀拼個你死我活，開始的時候必須潛水到右面拿到鑰匙才能繼續前進。 Major topics includes the classical philosophy of death of plato , epicurus and the stoics ; the argument of immortality of the christian philosophy , descartes and kant ; the phenomenological analysis of death by heidegger , levinas and derrida ; and the chinese thought on death in confucianism and taoism主要課題包括：柏拉圖、伊壁鳩魯及斯多亞學派之死亡哲學；基督教哲學、笛卡兒及康德對不朽之討論；海德格、萊維納斯及德里達對死亡之現象學分析；以及儒家和道家之死亡思想。 For a year he had held this rank , and expected promotion on the first vacancy . in his regiment maximilian morrel was noted for his rigid observance , not only of the obligations imposed on a soldier , but also of the duties of a man ; and he thus gained the name of " the stoic .在他那一聯隊里，馬西米蘭莫雷爾是一個眾所周知最嚴守紀律的人，不僅嚴守一個軍人應盡的義務，而且還嚴守一個人應盡的責任，所以他獲得了“斯多葛派”斯多葛派是古希臘一種唯心主義哲學派別，擯棄享樂，提介寡欲。 Said albert , evidently surprised at such a question from his companion ; " i think he is a delightful fellow , who does the honors of his table admirably ; who has travelled much , read much , is , like brutus , of the stoic school , and moreover , " added he , sending a volume of smoke up towards the ceiling , " that he has excellent cigars .阿爾貝說道，他顯然很驚奇他的同伴會提出這樣一個問題。 “我覺得他是一個很有趣的人，他吃東西很講究，他到過很多地方，讀過很多書，而且，象布魯特斯一樣，也是一個堅忍主義者再說， ”他向天花板吐出一大股煙，然後才說， “他還有上等的雪茄。 ” 用"the stoic"造句  
百科解釋The Stoic is a novel by Theodore Dreiser, first published in 1947. It is the conclusion to A Trilogy of Desire, his series of novels about Frank Cowperwood, a businessman based on the real-life streetcar tycoon Charles Yerkes.詳細百科解釋


